The grim discovery follows the arrests of three people in the area after drivers affiliated to two taxi associations opened fire on each other. JOHANNESBURG - A body of a man has been found in Orlando in Soweto on Tuesday afternoon.The grim discovery follows the arrests of three people in the area after drivers affiliated to two taxi associations opened fire on each other.Taxi operations there were disrupted as a result.It's unclear whether the murder is related to the taxi violence.The police's Kay Makhubela said: He appears to have been killed elsewhere and thrown in the water. But at the moment we don t know who he is and what the motive behind his death is. 